    <string name="STRID_FUNC_STRS_SHOOTING_TIPS_PAGE3_HEADER">Test Shot</string>
    <string name="STRID_FUNC_STRS_SHOOTING_TIPS_PAGE1_CONTENTS">Search the brightest star and set the focus targeting that star.\nUsing Focus Magnifier is effective to check the focus in detail.\n\nIf you can not find the target star in the direction you want to shoot, find the target star in other direction, set the focus, and pan the device in the direction you want to shoot.</string>
    <string name="STRID_FUNC_STRS_SHOOTING_TIPS_PAGE2_CONTENTS">Effective using largest magnification of Focus Magnifier centering the targeted star. \nBy turning the focusing ring of the lens, set the target star as clear as possible.\nWhen targeted star is hard to view, reduce the F-value (opening the aperture).\n(Theme: Custom only)\n\nRe-adjust the focus when zoom position is changed.</string>
    <string name="STRID_FUNC_STRS_SHOOTING_TIPS_PAGE3_CONTENTS">Test Shot function helps create balanced arrangement and exposure.\nAlso useful for checking the focus by enlarging the view.\n\nYou can activate Test Shot function from Focus Magnifier, MF Assist and Shooting mode.\n\nAfter the shutter release, Auto Review will activate.\nTest shot image will not be saved. </string>
    <string name="STRID_FUNC_STRS_TEST_SHOT">Test Shot</string>
